## ğŸ¯ Task A: Gender Classification from Face Images

---

### ğŸ“ Dataset Structure

Organized in two folders â€” one for training and one for validation â€” each containing subfolders `male/` and `female/`:

```
/Comys_Hackathon5/Task A/
â”œâ”€â”€ train/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ female/
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ male/
â”œâ”€â”€ val/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ female/
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ male/
```

---

### ğŸ§  Model Architecture

| Component        | Description                                      |
|------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| **Base Model**    | MobileNetV2 (pretrained on ImageNet)            |
| **Input Shape**   | `(256, 256, 3)`                                  |
| **Trainable Layers** | Only last 30 layers of MobileNetV2             |
| **Top Layers**    | GlobalAveragePooling2D â†’ Dense(128, ReLU) â†’ Dropout(0.5) â†’ Dense(1, Sigmoid) |
| **Loss**          | Binary Crossentropy                              |
| **Optimizer**     | Adam (learning rate: default)                    |
| **Class Weights** | Applied: `{0: 2.44, 1: 0.63}` to balance gender classes |
| **Image Augmentation** | Rotation, Zoom, Flip applied via `tf.keras.layers` |

---

### âš™ï¸ How to Run

1. Upload this notebook to [Google Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/)
